        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-10-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-11-09T13:00:00-05:00" n="289" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d289">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>In a memorandum of January 9, not printed, the Chinese Embassy informed the
                    Department of State that the Chinese Government welcomed the proposal of the
                    United States to expedite deliveries of reparations from Japan by issuing
                    interim directives to the Supreme <pb facs="0361" n="347" xml:id="pg_347"/>
                    Commander for the Allied Forces in Japan, and it called attention to certain
                    special requirements for China’s reconstruction. (740.00119 PW/1–947)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
